cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.DC

This paper deals with wireless network security and attacks, specifically Evil Twins and device to device attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves wireless networks and communication, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the implementation of a detection mechanism, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of technology and hardware, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
